To create a LaTeX code that represents a FEN (Forsyth-Edwards Notation) chessboard, you can use the `chessboard` package and the `picture` environment. Below is an example of how to create a FEN board using LaTeX:
```latex
\RequirePackage{chessboard}
\RequirePackage{graphicx}

\begin{document}

\begin{picture}(100,100)
  \chessboard[fen="rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1"]
\end{picture}

\end{document}
```
In this code, the `chessboard` package is required to generate the chessboard, and the `graphicx` package is required for the `picture` environment. The FEN notation is defined using the `chessboard` package, which takes the FEN string as an argument. The `picture` environment is used to enclose the chessboard, and the `rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1` string is the FEN notation for the position. Note that you should replace the FEN string with the actual FEN notation for the chessboard you want to represent.

